# v0.5.8 Release Plan

**Theme**: Transaction fee consistency + stale port/config cleanup + remove legacy messaging duplicates + fix broken systemd services — finish the fee-standardization work started in v0.5.5 (which fixed `transaction_service.py` and `agent_stream.py` but missed 3 other locations still using `1000`), fix the stale `HERMES_COORDINATOR_URL` default port, remove the legacy blockchain-polling `agent_daemon.py` and orphaned `hermes_polling_daemon.py` (both duplicates of the WebSocket `ping_handler`), and fix three systemd service issues found during a full service-file audit (missing env file, missing PYTHONPATH, duplicate marketplace service overwriting production).

**Goal**: Ensure every code path that computes a coin-request balance check or signs a transfer transaction uses the canonical blockchain fee of `10` (not `1000`), so valid transactions are no longer rejected with spurious "insufficient balance" errors. Fix the Hermes service's default coordinator URL so it points at the Agent Coordinator (8107) instead of a defunct port (8011). Remove both legacy/orphaned messaging daemons (`agent_daemon.py` no-op with `--address ""`, `hermes_polling_daemon.py` never deployed) and all references. Fix the agent-coordinator env file not being created by setup.sh (service won't start on fresh install). Fix ffmpeg service missing PYTHONPATH (ModuleNotFoundError on start). Remove the legacy duplicate marketplace service file that runs as root and overwrites the hardened production version during `link-systemd.sh`.

**Context**: This release addresses residual issues surfaced by a codebase analysis of the Hermes / Agent Coordinator / agent-daemon messaging path, followed by an exhaustive fee search across all services and a full systemd service-file audit. v0.5.5 already resolved the router scoping bug, the `transaction_service.py` and `agent_stream.py` fee defaults, and marked `agent_daemon.py` as legacy in its docstring. v0.5.8 finishes that cleanup: removing both legacy daemons, fixing the remaining fee mismatches, the stale default port, and three service-file bugs that prevent services from starting correctly on fresh installs.

**Status**: All 8 changes implemented. Tasks #1 + #4b (fee fixes) done by Agent A. Tasks #2, #3, #4a, #5, #6, #7, #8 done by Agent B. All verification greps pass, `systemd-analyze verify` clean on all touched service files. The `1000→10` fee fix is temporary — v0.5.10 implements a hard fork changing the unit system to compute-seconds (1 AIT = 3600), at which point the fee changes from `10` to `36`. See `docs/releases/v0.5.10/change.log`.

