### 7. Remove Legacy `scripts/systemd/` Directory

**Problem:** `scripts/systemd/` is a legacy folder. All app service files should live in their respective app directory under `apps/`. The directory contains 2 files, both problematic:

**7a. Duplicate marketplace service (overwrites production):**

Two `aitbc-marketplace.service` files exist with different configurations:

| | `apps/marketplace/aitbc-marketplace.service` | `scripts/systemd/aitbc-marketplace.service` |
|---|---|---|
| User | `aitbc` | `root` |
| Port | `8104` (explicit) | none (code default) |
| Security hardening | Full (ProtectSystem, etc.) | Minimal |
| PYTHONPATH | `/opt/aitbc:...marketplace/src:...aitbc-core/src` | `/opt/aitbc:...marketplace/src` |

`scripts/utils/link-systemd.sh` scans `apps/*/aitbc-*.service` first (line 194), then `scripts/*/aitbc-*.service` second (line 243). Both use `ln -sf`, so the **second scan overwrites the first**. This means `scripts/systemd/aitbc-marketplace.service` (User=root, no port, minimal security) **silently replaces** `apps/marketplace/aitbc-marketplace.service` (User=aitbc, port 8104, hardened) on every `link-systemd.sh` run.

The `scripts/systemd/` version is legacy — v0.5.5 §4 already switched the marketplace service to direct execution and the `apps/` version reflects those changes. The `scripts/systemd/` version was not updated and is dead.

**7b. Recovery service (orphan, needs relocating):**

`scripts/systemd/aitbc-recovery.service` is an infrastructure oneshot service that runs `link-systemd.sh` + `load-keystore-secrets.sh` on boot. It has no `apps/` counterpart (it's a system utility, not an app). It's actively used — listed in `infra_services` in `link-systemd.sh` (lines 79, 87). It needs to move to `scripts/utils/` where the scripts it invokes already live.

**Fix:**
- Delete `scripts/systemd/aitbc-marketplace.service` (the `apps/marketplace/` version is authoritative)
- Move `scripts/systemd/aitbc-recovery.service` → `scripts/utils/aitbc-recovery.service`
- Delete the now-empty `scripts/systemd/` directory
- No change needed to `link-systemd.sh` — it already scans `scripts/utils/aitbc-*.service` (line 243), so the moved recovery service will be picked up automatically

**Files deleted:**
- `scripts/systemd/aitbc-marketplace.service` — legacy duplicate, runs as root, overwrites production version
- `scripts/systemd/` — the now-empty legacy directory

**Files moved:**
- `scripts/systemd/aitbc-recovery.service` → `scripts/utils/aitbc-recovery.service`

**Note:** Other infrastructure services in `scripts/maintenance/` (backup), `scripts/monitoring/` (monitoring), and `scripts/utils/` (load-secrets, plugin) are correctly placed — they're system utilities with no app counterpart, in semantically appropriate subdirectories. Only `scripts/systemd/` is the legacy folder.

**Tests:**
- Run `link-systemd.sh` and verify:
  - `aitbc-marketplace` symlink points to `apps/marketplace/aitbc-marketplace.service` (not overwritten)
  - `aitbc-recovery` symlink points to `scripts/utils/aitbc-recovery.service`
- Verify `systemctl cat aitbc-marketplace` shows `User=aitbc` and `MARKETPLACE_BIND_PORT=8104`
- Verify `scripts/systemd/` directory no longer exists

