## Open Questions (Resolved)

1. **Commented-out coordinator-api hermes context routers** — **RESOLVED: deferred to v0.5.9 §7.** Investigation found the 4 router files (`hermes_decision.py`, `hermes_enhanced_simple.py`, `hermes_health.py`, `hermes_resource.py`) are fully implemented but in the wrong service (coordinator-api has nothing to do with agent messaging), reachable only through dead code (`core/routers.py` is never called), and have no tests. v0.5.9 merges the Hermes service into the Agent Coordinator and deletes these routers — if decision/health/resource functionality is needed, it should be built as Agent Coordinator handlers, not resurrected from coordinator-api. See `docs/releases/v0.5.9/change.log` §7.

2. **Add `HERMES_DB_PATH` to example node.env files?** — **Not addressed.** `examples/node.env.open-island` doesn't set it, so deployments based on that example rely on the code default. Low severity; left as-is.

3. **Fee unit system (1000x documentation error)** — **RESOLVED: deferred to v0.5.10.** The v0.5.8 `1000→10` fix eliminates the immediate mismatch causing transaction rejections. v0.5.10 implements the proper unit system (1 AIT = 3600 compute-seconds, fee = 36 = 0.01 AIT), which is the real fix for the v0.5.6 docs saying "0.01 AIT per transaction". See `docs/releases/v0.5.10/change.log`.

